. The book also argues that these remains do not just pose practical conservation problems but also philosophical dilemmas, compounded by the critical debate on if - and how - they should be displayed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchaeologyzEurope. 0aBog bodiesvExhibitionsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aBog bodieszEurope, Northern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aBog bodies.  aBogs.  aConservation.  aExecution.  aMummies.  aMuseums.  aOfferings.  aPreserved remains.  aSacrifice.  aViolence.1 aGiles, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526150196zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526150196zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526150196/original  a978-3-11-128198-8 Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA